Your words are appreciated, Your
Highness. Though, Yuwel deserves

And so, she became the Demon

I tried twice and lost. Only the fact

95: She lives for the blade, and I for Tris.

Both as her brother and lord... I wish I

...I see. Though, the way you talk

128:
The Captain of the Swallow Knights

146:
I've wanted to break that icy stare of

159:
Marvelous! That's the Cieldeau I
know!
163:
And Yuwel, you put up a brilliant

167:
...Thank you for saying so. Phew, that

171:
Hmph... I could say the same. I didn't
expect to need such power.
174:
I expected a mere warm-up, but
that was entertaining.
179:
Your sister told me that you're at
your best when acting as a
swordsman.
182:
I don't know about that, but... I prefer

190:
Just that neither you nor I can keep

194:
...As if I could be compared to a
Nouin.
198:
There's nothing wrong with

202:

208:
I can be just as stubborn as either of

225:
Hmph... Come then, if you believe
you can break the Blade of Tris!
234:
I was inspired by His Highness and
the House of Nouin. As lord of Tris, I
have to play my part.
239:
Besides, I benefited a bit more than I
expected. Perhaps I should even
thank you.
244: I've thought about this as well...
247:
We have the power to get the
houses to act. Even mobilizing the

His Highness.
250:
...You're in quite the convenient
position, don't you think?
255:
I'm right where I need to be. I
specialize in marching through mud,
remember?
259:
That's not at all how your sister
would act...
263:
And you act nothing like your
brother. Show some dignity, Captain!
273:
Warriors of Tris, forge a path!
Swallow Knights, clear the way!
276:
Together, for our future! Charge
down the path of light!
